                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d764">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/2023a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-26T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1736. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_CTL1">Chadbourne</persName>
                    [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 337. War Trade Board on suggestion of General <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PGJJ1">Pershing</persName> has authorized
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> to put
                    himself at disposal of A.E.F. in undertaking the purchase of horses and mules in
                    Spain. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> is
                    advised that War Trade Board is prepared to support him fully either in exerting
                    economic pressure upon Spain, or in granting concessions to Spain, as may seem
                    best, and that it is prepared to take up the matter of securing vigorous and
                    joint representation to Spain by Ambassadors there of Associated Governments. We
                    are confident that <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName> will be much aided by the cooperation of your
                    organization, which we have advised he may confidently rely on.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
